  "text": "Bahari et al. [CITATION_1] proposed i-vector model for each utterance and utilized least squares support vector regression (LSSVR) for speaker age estimation. Their work was tested on telephone conversation of national institute for standard and technology (NIST, 2010) . Our work also differs from Bahari et al.'s work. While Bahari et al. attempted to regress the age of the speaker regardless of the speaker's gender, we attempt to classify the speaker age and gender at the same time. Moreover, their work depends on i-vector to represent each speaker utterance however our work uses the DNN to extract the features and to build speaker models.",
